8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 572, L.D. 886, “An Act to Regulate
10 Medication Abortions”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1598-A by striking out all of subsection 2 (page 1, lines
12 11 to 25 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
13 '2. Medication abortions; duties of health care professional. The following
14 provisions apply to medication abortions.
15 A. A health care professional who prescribes a chemical agent or drug to be used by a
16 patient for a medication abortion shall oversee the patient's ingestion of the chemical
17 agent or drug in person.
18 B. A health care professional overseeing a medication abortion shall inform the
19 patient:
20 (1) Of the steps involved in the medication abortion;
21 (2) What the patient will experience following ingestion of the chemical agent or
22 drug for the medication abortion;
23 (3) Of any physical or emotional risk of undergoing the medication abortion; and
24 (4) Of any chemical agent, drug or other means by which the medication abortion
25 may be reversed.
26 3. Medication abortions; duties of manufacturer or distributor; penalty. A person
27 may not sell or distribute a chemical agent or drug used for a medication abortion to an
28 individual in the State through an online source unless the manufacturer or distributor
29 confirms that the individual has a prescription for the chemical agent or drug from a health
30 care professional.
31 A. A person that violates this subsection is subject to a civil penalty not to exceed
32 $1,000 for each violation.
