COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 572, L.D. 886
1 B. In lieu of or in addition to the collection of civil penalties under paragraph A, the
2 Attorney General may bring a civil action in the Superior Court to prevent, restrain or
3 enjoin a violation of this subsection.'
4 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
5 number to read consecutively.
6 SUMMARY
77 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, makes the following
88 changes to the bill.
99 1. It removes the provision of the bill prohibiting a person from purchasing a chemical
1100 agent or drug used for a medication abortion from online sources. Instead, it prohibits a
1111 person from selling or distributing to an individual a chemical agent or drug used for a
1122 medication abortion using online sources unless the individual has a prescription from a
1133 licensed health care professional. It authorizes the Attorney General to bring a civil action
1144 seeking an injunction and civil penalties against a person that violates this prohibition.
1155 2. It clarifies that a licensed health care professional who prescribes a chemical agent
1166 or drug for a medication abortion must be present in person when the patient ingests the
1177 chemical agent or drug.
1188 3. It removes the requirement that a licensed health care professional inform a patient
1199 of any spiritual risks of undergoing a medication abortion.
